nge of thinkers, including Kant, Hegel, Fanon, Emerson, Du Bois, Senghor, and Suzuki. This book not only breaks with disciplinary conventions about period and geography but also argues that these conventions obscure our ability to understand the modern condition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aSelf (Philosophy)xHistory. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Comparative Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438473864423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438473864/original  a978-3-11-149143-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles